data: After Sam and Cat babysit Benny, he says while walking out, "You are the best babysitter ever!", but doesn't specify who. After Sam and Cat argue over who he was talking about, they decide to make their next appointment a competition to see who is the better babysitter and the winner gets the master bedroom. When they babysit Daisy, Jarvis, and Sophie, Sam and Cat each do awesome things to get the kids to like them. When Sam and Cat asks them which of the two they liked better, it turned out to be a tie since Sophie didn't want to choose and thought that they are best as a team, rather than individually. Sam & Cat then split up the master bedroom. Continuity: In the end of the episode when the master bedroom has been done in the styles of both Sam and Cat, there is a picture of Hollywood Arts teacher and recurring character in Victorious, Mr. Sikowitz.

Sam and Cat gets a break from babysitting, but to Dice's request, they babysit Goomer while he goes to Phoenix for a day for hair modeling. The day before Goomer's big match against the "Skull Crusher" (John Zakappa), things don't go as planned when Cat accidentally blinds him when she puts his tongue drops in his eyes. During the competition, Goomer doesn't do so well as he has trouble seeing, but wins the match after he is enraged when the "Skull Crusher" (John Zakappa) makes fun of Dice's hair. Guest Stars: Zoran Korach as Goomer Continuity: Sam mentions the events from the previous episode "#NewGoat", when Dice employed the girls to babysit a pet goat.

When Sam and Cat make a commercial for their business that features Dice's dog "Opee", a rich family goes to their apartment and claim the dog is theirs because they lost it six months ago when Dice found it in an ally and they demand it back. Their dog is so important to them because they've entered a dog competition for the past years. When they don't get the dog back, they threaten to come back the next day with a court order and a policeman so they can get it back. Sam and Cat go to dog shelters, trying to find an identical dog. They find a dog that looks exactly like Opee but the owner of the shelter says he's vicious. After they give the identical dog to the family, their daughter re-enters the dog dancing competition and the dog ends up attacking her on live television. Continuity: Sam mentions when she and Gibby were stuck in an elevator on iCarly. Continuity 2: The family's dog's name is "Cornelius", which was Gibby's middle name.

Dice gives Cat a drink to help her focus so she can study for a big test while he, Goomer and Sam go to a mixed-martial arts fight. After Cat has too much of the drink, she falls asleep and wakes up with lost memory and find her hair dyed blue, her hand hand-cuffed to a small, angry, foreign man and Sam's motorcycle missing. They get information from Nona at Elderly Acres, where Cat got her hair dyed, and look through the security footage at Bots. They find out that John Zakappa stole the motorcycle and Cat handcuffed herself to his foreign friend. They meet up with him to retrieve the motorcycle in exchange for his foreign friend and end up tricking him to get the motorcycle and keep his friend hostage. Guest Stars: Zoran Korach as Goomer Continuity: This episode mentions details from #RevengeOfTheBritBrats and #GoomerSitting. Note: This is John Zakappa's second appearance.

When Sam finds a safe in their closet, she tries to find the combination while she and Cat have to watch Dice. He says he wants to go to a poker game with a bunch of college friends but after they won't let him, Sam finally opens the safe. She and Cat go in and discover a hidden room, Dice locks them in so he can go hang out with his friends. After a couple of hours, Goomer shows up at the apartment and Sam and Cat yell for him to let them out, which he does. They find out Goomer knows where Dice is and they leave to go find him. They discover Dice was really dancing as entertainment at a little girls birthday party. They take him back to the apartment and punish him by locking him in the hidden room. Guest Stars: Zoran Korach as Goomer

Among the most recognizable features of Milan is its Virgin Mary. Better known as the “Madonnina” and located high above the city’s main Cathedral, the statue lends its name to one of the world’s most exciting football rivalries: the derby della Madonnina between Interistas and Milanistas. A priest, a fashion designer, a taxi driver, a journalist and a professional gambler – these colorful characters represent the inherent emotion behind this world-renowned matchup.

Barcelona is the center of a region that has always been, at least in spirit, its own nation with its own identity and beliefs within Spain. FC Barcelona, with legends like Johan Cruyff and modern-day greats like Xavi Hernández, is the city's pride and joy. Its style of play brings admirers from all over the world, but for the locals the team is a representation of Catalonia - més que un club (more than a club). The city stops whenever the team faces RCD Espanyol in El derbi barcelonés or Real Madrid in El Clásico.

In the streets of Bogota, there is one dream shared by the Colombian youth. They dream of becoming professional football players and becoming part of the tradition that their heroes from Independiente Santa Fe and Millonarios are a part of. Although the city is divided between those that support Los Cardenales and those who support El Ballet Azul, the two rivals live under the same roof - the legendary Estadio Nemesio Camacho 'El Campín." With a capacity of 40, 343 spectators, the stadium has hosted numerous editions of the Clásico Capitalino, the 2001 Copa America Final where Colombia defeated Mexico, and the 2011 U-20 World Cup.

In the 19th century, Manchester became famous for becoming the world's first industrialized city. Soon after, the industrialization period gave light to the city's identity - football. Manchester United and Manchester City, each founded in the 1800s, are rooted in a pair of iron and railroad companies. More than a century later, the two teams are on top of the game - Manchester City won its first Premier League title in 44 years in 2012, a year after Manchester won its 19th title.

Today, Mexico City is home to a new wave of warriors that play in a modern-day temple - the Aztec Stadium, the world's largest football-specific stadium and the only one to have hosted two World Cup finals. Mexico City's massive population is divided into three groups: the azulcremas of Club América, the cementeros of Cruz Azul, and the felinos of UNAM.

data: Following the storm, the doctors of Grey + Sloan Memorial attempt to care for victims, but soon find the ER overrun. Richard remains unconscious in the basement after receiving a severe electric shock and Bailey sends Shane to find him. Shane, however, passes the task over to Heather in an attempt to steal her surgery with Derek. Heather spots Richard on the basement floor, but she is also electrocuted when she hastily rushes to help him. The pair are later discovered and Derek and Shane begin trying to save Heather, while Cristina and Bailey attempt to revive Richard. Meredith remains sidelined after giving birth to her son. Arizona desperately attempts to make amends following her one-night stand, but Callie is unwilling to listen to her. Cristina and Owen clash about Richard's treatment and discover that Richard has made Meredith responsible for his medical decisions. Arizona returns home and discovers that Callie has packed up and moved out.

Derek fails in his attempts to save Heather, leaving Shane feeling responsible for his colleague's death. The interns are tasked with comforting Heather's mother when she arrives, but realize that they had been bad friends to her, and resolve to look out for each other more. Bailey and Catherine clash over how to proceed with Richard's condition, with Bailey wanting to perform risky surgery. Meredith ultimately accepts responsibility for Richard's care and allows Bailey to follow her instincts, saving Richard's life. Jackson rejects April following her declaration of love and she decides to go ahead with her engagement to Matthew. Owen and Cristina struggle to stay apart following their split. Arizona tracks Callie down to Meredith's house but Callie is again unforgiving and informs Arizona that they will now take turns caring for Sofia. Arizona later returns, desperate to see Sofia and while Callie initially refuses, Cristina urges her to not bring Sofia into the fight, resulting in Arizona being granted five minutes with her daughter.

The storm has passed, but the damage still remains. Callie and Arizona agreed to attend marriage counseling, but Callie, who’s still bitter and not hiding it at all, decides she doesn’t want to go, but Arizona should. Derek and Meredith are on leave to take care of their new baby and they are having quite a time adjusting to their new life. The group of interns is beginning to study for their residency exams, and April anxiously waits to hear about the results of her board exams, which she finally passes. Cristina and Alex pair up to do a heart valve repair, but resolve that the patient needs to be put on a transplant list. Meanwhile, Cristina encourages Alex to have sex with Jo. In her own failing relationship, she tells Owen that it’s time to start seeing other people, to which he replies, “I’ll try.” Owen and Avery butt heads over hospital finance issues: Owen wants money to fix the hospital and Avery wants money for surgeries. Webber needs a feeding tube to survive, but Bailey has an alternative, less effective, plan that will save Webber’s dignity but not his life. Shane takes charge and puts one in, despite Bailey’s stance. Webber tells Meredith that he picked the wrong person to be in charge of his health decisions, meaning he expected her to just let him die and not bring him back to life.

To raise money to repair the damage done to Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital, the doctors are dressed to the nines and throwing a fundraiser gala. Interns Shane and Stephanie are left to tend the pit by themselves, which forces them to become surgery sharks. All is going well at the gala, until an entertainer falls on top of the gala organizer, resulting in serious injuries. The doctors of Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital jump right in and become doctors once again. Meanwhile, April and Arizona stay in the supply closet trading relationship stories and drinking champagne. Alex leaves Jo at the gala, after seeing a junkie—whom he thinks is his dad—ushered into the ER. He decides to do a paternity test to find out, and in the middle of his telling Jo that he doesn’t want to know if the junkie is his dad or not, Jo blurts it out that he is. Cristina and Owen’s breakup becomes more real after a doctor from Seattle Presbyterian starts flirting with Owen at the gala. Then later that day, she looks for Owen again, making Cristina take a further step back. Bailey is stuck between a rock and a hard place, rather, two difficult patients: one who has cancer that can’t be treated, and Dr. Webber who has multiple options of treatment but doesn’t want to pursue any of them. Her solution is to make them roommates in hopes of them changing each other’s mind. Meredith and Derek, who have been on leave from the hospital, return and rediscover their love for surgeries.

Cristina and Owen’s breakup becomes more real after a doctor from Seattle Presbyterian starts flirting with Owen at the gala. Then later that day, she looks for Owen again, making Cristina take a further step back. Bailey is stuck between a rock and a hard place, rather, two difficult patients: one who has cancer that can’t be treated, and Dr. Webber who has multiple options of treatment but doesn’t want to pursue any of them. Her solution is to make them roommates in hopes of them changing each other’s mind. Meredith and Derek, who have been on leave from the hospital, return and rediscover their love for surgeries.

To raise money to repair the damage done to Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital, the doctors are dressed to the nines and throwing a fundraiser gala. Interns Shane and Stephanie are left to tend the pit by themselves, which forces them to become surgery sharks. All is going well at the gala, until an entertainer falls on top of the gala organizer, resulting in serious injuries. The doctors of Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital jump right in and become doctors once again. Meanwhile, April and Arizona stay in the supply closet trading relationship stories and drinking champagne. Alex's dad is still at Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital, and Jo is doing everything she can to mend the relationship between Alex and his dad. Meredith teams up with Cristina to do groundbreaking surgery—a heart/liver transplant, but due to unfortunate circumstances (having to breast pump and console Zola after she gets hurt), Meredith is unprepared, unfocused, and late to her surgery. Cristina confronts Meredith and says that they're in different places and they want different things, and that's okay, but she’s not willing to let up like Meredith. In turn, Meredith gets upset with Derek for making her miss her surgery because he didn't answer his phone. Stephanie and Jackson were having sex in the on-call room and were awkwardly discovered by Catherine, which drives a wedge between Stephanie and Catherine. Webber, with the help and urging from Catherine, returns to his old self—a take-charge kind of guy, ordering the residents around. Leah, after a night of bonding with Arizona, feels like someone at Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital actually "gets" her; however, Arizona remembers nothing about that night due to being drunk. Callie has a revelation with her patient’s "donor sister" that "you can say 'no'," so Callie kicks Arizona out of her apartment and celebrates by dancing in her underwear.

It’s time for Meredith to decide what her topic of research will be, and after much debate, she decides that she’s going to continue her mother’s research by taking it in a new direction. Derek and Callie have teamed up to work on a brain mapping project, but Callie (who wants to “move back into her place”) feels like she should be working with regenerative cartilage. However, Derek persuades her to rejoin him. Webber uses his condition to teach Jo, the now second year resident, how to be a better doctor. She is finally able to diagnose the cause the of his shoulder pain: a pancreatic pseudocyst. Because he has taken a professional liking to Cristina, and she to him as well, Shane reveals to Derek that he no longer has any interest in working with him on his brain mapping project. Cristina takes an interest in Meredith's research, but Meredith, who is still hurt by what Cristina said to her, doesn't take it kindly. Alex takes a step to get closer to his dad, and while they’re jamming on their guitars, Alex’s dad tells him that he has family in Florida. Surprisingly to Alex, it’s not his family. Leah tells her fellow residents that she had a fling with Arizona, and while Arizona initially fights her feelings for Leah, she succumbs to her feelings of loneliness and texts her. Derek tells Meredith that he’s going to take a step back from his work to allow Meredith to have a great year.

It’s Halloween at Grey + Sloan Memorial Hospital, and things are getting creepy! A delusional, psychotic drug addict, who has a condition where his heart is on the opposite side of his chest, makes his way into the ER after he was shot multiple times because he was eating the face of another patient; Jackson and April work together to repair the patient’s face injuries. A ghost-like patient of Dr. Brooks finds herself in need of help, but she demands that she’ll only see Dr. Brooks until Shane tells her Brooks is dead. Cristina and Owen team up to do surgery on the zombie-like drug addict, and they find out that they can be in the same room together as long as they don’t overcomplicate it. Alex and Jo are on another Peds case and save a little girl from being literally “scared to death.” Webber kicks Bailey off his case, and he reappoints Meredith—after an apology of course—and tells her he wants her to help him teach the 2nd year residents. Ben returns to surprise Bailey and Tuck for Halloween, and while repairing Zola’s costume, Ben gives Shepherd an idea for his research. Ben later springs it on Bailey that he has dropped out of his residency to spend more time with her. Leah and Arizona get closer as they share their common fear of contracting diseases from patients.

data: July 27 – Friedrich Wilhelm Karl Ludwig Georg Alfred Alexander is born in Neustrelitz
Marries Louise Auguste Stephanie Beyrich, later von Schönau, mother to three of his children

Commissioner General of the first colony that the society proposed to establish in Texas July 1 – Arrives in Galveston, purchases land on Matagorda Bay to be called Carlshafen, or Indianola

Secures title to acres (km2) of the Veramendi grant, including the Comal Springs and River, for the Adelsverein March 21 – Founds New Braunfels May 15 – Returns to Germany December 3 – Marries the widow Maria Josephine Sophie, widow of Prince Franz of Salm-Salm and princess of Lowenstein-Wertheim-Rosenberg, mother to five of Carl's children

data: In the 90-minute series premiere, Jo arrives at the home of the Quinn-Davises. Both parents have children from previous marriages, and tension has reached a limit. Their daughters Emily and Amber have chosen not to follow the rules or give their parents respect. Their son Derek has become low spirited due to all the fighting within the home. Chad has overcome his addiction and is recovering. Julie and Don, the parents, each defend their children— which sets a divide that is heading towards divorce. While Jo is visiting, Chad receives some horrifying news regarding a close friend and Amber struggles with alcohol consumption.

data: After the declaration of Plan of Tacubaya, Congress declared that he was no longer president but he was recognized by conservatives as president with absolute powers.
After disowning Comonfort, Zuloaga was appointed president by the Conservative Party.
He assumed the conservative presidency as a substitute when Zuloaga left office.
As president of the Supreme Court of the conservative government, he took office for two days when Miramón left office.

He took office as interim president of the conservative government after he was elected by a group of "Representatives of the States" who supported the conservatives. He was defeated at the Battle of Calpulalpan, resigned the presidency and fled the country.
Despite having been defeated, the conservatives appointed Zuloaga as president until December 28, when they recognized the Regency who was seeking to reestablish the Mexican Empire.

table-1280-325.caption: Expurgation
data: Got up at 20 m. to 9. My dearest Albert put on my stockings for me. I went in and saw him shave; a great delight for me. We breakfasted at ½ p.9 together. Wrote to Lord M in A.'s room. Sang to him. Dressed &c. I passed through the middle room where Lord Melbourne was with Albert. Wrote my journal. A. and I went to see Ma.. At 20 m. to 1 Albert, my dearest Albert, drove me out in the Pony carriage, the ladies following in carriages, and the gentlemen on horseback; we met Papa driving the Duchess of Sutherland; we met the Hounds, coming home; Ernest in a red coat and top boots; and in high spirits at the Hunt. It was a lovely day; we came home at 10 m. p.2. At ½ p.2 we all lunched in the Oak room. Mama came to our rooms, and then Ernest came and stayed with us. At 5 m. p.4 Lord Melbourne came to me and stayed with me till 5 m. to 5. He was not very well; talked of our having driven out; there being bad news from China; ...

We went to see Mama after breakfast & I wrote my Journal, &c. — Before 1, dearest Albert drove me out in the Pony Phaeton, the Ladies following in carriages, & the Gentlemen on horseback. We met Papa driving the Dss of Sutherland, & the Hounds coming back, Ernest in a red coat & top boots, in high spirits at the Hunt. It was a lovely day. — We all lunched in the Oak Rooms. Mama afterwards came to our rooms, & then Ernest came & stayed with us. — Saw Ld Melbourne, before 4, who stayed with me nearly an hour. Talked of there being bad news from China; ...

data: American Window Glass trust purchased Hartford City Glass Company in 1899. Glass blowing machinery gradually caused employee counts to decrease. Superior technology used by competitors caused difficulties for the company during the 1920s. The Hartford City plant was closed in 1929, although the company kept a few other plants open.
Former Jones Glass Company purchased by American Window Glass Company. Employee count of 65 in 1903. Plant was sold in 1905.
Employee count of 65 for window glass maker in 1903. In Vincennes, company employed 200 in 1950.
Started by James Clelland and J.R. Johnston in 1901 after they purchased the Hurrle Glass Works. Employee count of 67 for 1903. Closed in 1905. Purchased at auction by J. R. Johnston in 1905.
Bottle maker employed 90 in 1901. Factory was destroyed by fire in 1905. Moved to Jackson, Ohio.

Founded in 1929 by ex-Johnston Glass plant manager George T. Fulton. Hartford City plant destroyed by fire in 1966. Company headquarters continued in Hartford City whlle the Vincinnes plant still operated. Sold in 1986.
Produced bottles and jars. Employed 75 in 1903. Plant destroyed by fire in 1904, but rebuilt. Moved to Ohio by 1908.

One of largest window glass makers in world during the 1890s. Plant occupied acres (ha), and was "the largest grinding and chipping establishment in the United States" in 1896. Purchased by American Window Glass and became plant number 3.
Window glass, mirrors. Operated by Reidy family.
Window glass factory started by Charles J. Hurrle and investors in 1898. Employee count of 60 in 1901. Sold in 1901 to James Clelland and J.R. Johnston to start Clelland Glass Company.
Window glass company founded by former secretary and plant manager of Hartford City Glass Company, J. R. Johnston. Also made ornamental, bent, and chipped glass. Employee count of 200 for 1903.
Window glass factory began in 1898 with a foreign workforce, and employed 60. Company was acquired by American Window Glass Company in 1899 and became factory number 32.
112 employees in 1910. Made glass bottles. Moved to Upland, Indiana, in 1911 when natural gas became depleted.
